channel.title: Broken my car or something
channel.description:
I drive my little car pretty dam hard. Theres an old moorland road near me, its deserted, but with some gravel and some tarmac areas. So naturally, i rally it with a few others.
Let me remind you, the road is deserted and technically closed, its called an "unadopted road" and no one uses because it dosn't really go anywhere. It leads onto a main road later on though.
Anyway, i drove it that hard i ruined the brakes haha. We play cat and mouse on the road, hitting 100MPH+, then hard on the brakes to 50MPH for a tight cornor. This is why i <3 hatchbacks. The video shows me going down along streight attemping to brake for before the main road. My foot was to the floor on the brakes at around 60MPH+ and nothing was happening. At the end i drop the camera to get ready for evasive haha.
[url]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ARtfGAYw55k[/url]
I thought it was pretty funny, although the brake warning light can be worrying. Brakes were fine once they cooled. Note: The stopping distance is NOT because of the wet and the fuel gauge is pretty much on 0 because i like to drive with a low fuel load to balence out the handling.

item.description:
Collision:

I got my car for $3000 AUD, thats about 1700 pounds.

It’s a rear wheel, 4L V6, does 600km to the tank and I have easily hit 200km/h (125m/h) in under 10 seconds in it.

The rear end it light as a feather when I have less then half a tank of fuel and will wheel spin at 2K RPM on a flat road.

How much did your’s cost?

Haha, oh wow. Its not the cost of the car in this country mate, you can pick up a nice BMW (few years old obv) for that. Its insurance mate. My insurance for my car (1.3ltr petrol) costs £1,300 a year.

Its that thats difficult to pay for mate! A 4L V6? Seriously, it would cost like £4,000 to get me insured on that for a year.
